locations: JFK (John F Kennedy International Airport, New York)
keyFacts: This document shows Jeffrey Epstein's extensive international travel history from 1991 to 2020, with 40 recorded entries.
Many flights originate from or arrive at JFK Airport in New York, with frequent destinations including London (LHR) and Paris (CDG).
Several entries are marked with 'P' indicating passport travel, while others use APIS (Advanced Passenger Information System) or are marked 'AIRLINE (NOT API)'.
The document was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on January 23, 2020, months after Epstein's death in August 2019.
Travel patterns show consistent international movement throughout the 1990s and 2000s, with flights to destinations including Tokyo, Sydney, Honolulu, and various European cities.
